The paper focuses on super-resolution in the context of multimedia, specifically image, video, and multi-dimensions. This suggests that it falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. Additionally, the paper surveys the literature on deep learning methods for super-resolution, indicating that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Finally, the paper discusses benchmarks and evaluation metrics, which could suggest a connection to graphics (cs.GR).
